        "CargoGradeToken": [
            "Small"
        ],
        "Contractor|HaulCargo_MultiToSingle": [
            "Hello!\n\nThere\u2019s a load of cargo (<EM4>4 SCU</EM4> or smaller) that needs to be delivered to a freight elevator at <EM4>[Destination|Address]</EM4>. The only thing is that the cargo is spread across a few locations, which I\u2019ve listed out below.  \n\nPICK UP LOCATIONS (ANY ORDER)\n\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location1|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location2|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location3|Address]</EM4>\n\nMakes no difference what order you grab the stuff, as long as it\u2019s all delivered.\n\nBy the way, we strongly encourage contractors to bring a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> along.   \n\nCovalex Independent Contractors\n\nChase Hewitt\nJr. Logistics Coordinator\nCovalex Shipping  \n'Anything you need, anywhere you need it.'\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCovalex Shipping is a limited liability corporation. To encourage timely deliveries and prevent fraud on cargo hauls, Covalex Shipping will set a delivery time limit and upon expiration, any undelivered cargo will be considered stolen and treated as such. Total payment will be prorated according to the percentage of cargo successfully delivered.",
            "Hey,\n\nHere\u2019s an interesting one. <EM4>[Destination|Address]</EM4> is expecting a few shipments (max container size of <EM4>4 SCU</EM4>) so the data technicians bundled all the pick ups together. Here\u2019s a list of the stops: \n\nPICK UP LOCATIONS (ANY ORDER)\n\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location1|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location2|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location3|Address]</EM4>\n\nFeel free to do them in whatever order you want. Only thing that\u2019s important is that all of them get delivered to a freight elevator at [Destination].\n\nBy the way, we strongly encourage contractors to bring a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> along.   \n\nCovalex Independent Contractors\n\nChase Hewitt\nJr. Logistics Coordinator\nCovalex Shipping  \n'Anything you need, anywhere you need it.'\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCovalex Shipping is a limited liability corporation. To encourage timely deliveries and prevent fraud on cargo hauls, Covalex Shipping will set a delivery time limit and upon expiration, any undelivered cargo will be considered stolen and treated as such. Total payment will be prorated according to the percentage of cargo successfully delivered.",
            "Hi there,\n\nI\u2019m in a bind and hoping you can help. A trusted hauler signed up for a run that needs to be delivered ASAP, but their ship junked out right when they were about to launch so I need someone to take over this run right away.\n\nIt's all cargo <EM4>4 SCU</EM4> or smaller that needs to go to a freight elevator at <EM4>[Destination|Address]</EM4> after being collected from a few locations, which I\u2019ve listed below:\n\nPICK UP LOCATIONS (ANY ORDER)\n\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location1|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location2|Address]</EM4>\n- Freight elevator at <EM4>[Location3|Address]</EM4>\n\nThe delay has already caused issues at some of the pick up locations. They really need that cargo gone to free up space for new deliveries. Any chance you can collect everything above and deliver it as quick as possible?\n\nBy the way, we strongly encourage contractors to bring a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4> along.   \n\nCovalex Independent Contractors\n\nChase Hewitt\nJr. Logistics Coordinator\nCovalex Shipping  \n'Anything you need, anywhere you need it.'\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCovalex Shipping is a limited liability corporation. To encourage timely deliveries and prevent fraud on cargo hauls, Covalex Shipping will set a delivery time limit and upon expiration, any undelivered cargo will be considered stolen and treated as such. Total payment will be prorated according to the percentage of cargo successfully delivered."
        ],
